            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Gyaananda School is located in Sector 109, Dwarka Expressway, Gurugram. The school was established in 2017 and has been gaining popularity in the local area.\n\nThe school has a relatively small number of teachers, with only 22 teachers, out of which 68.18% are postgraduates. The student-teacher ratio of 16:1 is reasonable, and the classroom size of 11 students per class ensures that each student receives adequate attention.\n\nThe school offers English and Hindi as languages, making it accessible to students from diverse backgrounds. Gyaananda School is affiliated with CBSE, which ensures that students receive a quality education that is recognized nationally.\n\nThe annual fee range of 1lac to 1.62 lacs and transport fee range of 20k to 50k is reasonable compared to other schools in the area.\n\nThe school offers a range of sports facilities such as taekwondo, table tennis, chess, cricket, carrom, and skating, which is a positive aspect of the school.\n\nOverall, Gyaananda School is a decent choice for parents seeking a quality education for their children. The school has good infrastructure, offers a range of sports facilities, and is affiliated with CBSE.",
